<TITLE> BNP PP meeting cancelled after Saifur's death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com) - The BNP's parliamentary party meeting, scheduled for Saturday, was postponed after the death of veteran party leader and former finance minister M Saifur Rahman. Rahman died at Brahmanbaria Sadar Hospital following a road accident on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway on Saturday afternoon. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia expressed deep mourning over the death of the veteran opposition politician. Rahman, aged 77, was critically injured after his car crashed at Ghoriala just after 3pm, his personal assistant Shamsul Haque told bdnews24.com. He was rushed to the Sadar Hospital, where he was declared dead at around 3.30pm, doctors told bdnews24.com. BNP cancelled all party programmes for the day. The parliamentary party meeting had been scheduled to decide whether the main opposition party would be joining the third session of parliament beginning Sep 7. The party's chief whip Joynal Abdin Farrouque told bdnews24.com on Friday that all party MPs had been asked to attend the meeting that would have been chaired by BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia at her political office in Gulshan. BNP has been out of parliament since the better part of the inaugural session over a dispute over seat arrangements and other demands.
